cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving extractive summarization, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces pre-training tasks that involve learning to capture document-level context, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves experiments and evaluation, which could place it under information retrieval (cs.IR) or neural networks (cs.NE).
